nic humor and his warmth, which together balance his tough-mindedness. And even when he shows the human race caught in some vicious circle, he may be seen courageously seeking a way out and at times believing he has found it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aShort stories, American. 4aAmerican literature. 4aEnglish Literature. 4aliterature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  abermuda triangle.  adarker side of life.  adoubtful cosmic order.  aendlessly repeated events.  agod.  ahistory.  ahuman race.  ahumankind.  aironic humor.  anightmarish world events.  apersonal tragedies.  atough mindedness.  atreadmill.  auniversal food chain.  avast round of devourers.  avicious circle.  avictims.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052023893040uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520930223?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520930223423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520930223/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles